About
Crazy Horse is one of the most iconic cabarets in Paris (and the world). Housed in a former wine cellar, you'll be treated to a sensual and tantalizing cabaret show featuring nude female dancers, dizzying lights, and arresting tunes. There are many ways to experience the cabaret—get a standard show ticket or upgrade to the premium experience which includes dinner, champagne, caviar, and V.I.P. seats. For the full "Crazy" experience, you can even get a private guided tour by one of the Crazy Girls before the show. Before you leave, don’t forget to snap a photo with the iconic red lips sign at the entrance. – Tripadvisor

The area

Address
Neighborhood: Champs-Élysées
This area is characterized by its namesake avenue which extends northwest from the Louvre to the modern business district, punctuated by the iconic Arc de Triomphe. Grand embassies stand among impressive offices and presidential palaces; architecture from 19th century Universal Exhibitions, homes, art galleries, and 19th century streets designed by Baron Haussmann flank haute-couture boutiques. This neighborhood never rests, buzzing with visitors from around the world at all times of day and night, all within a stone's throw of the Seine.
How to get there
  • Alma – Marceau • 2 min walk
  • Pont de l'Alma • 5 min walk

    Best Cabaret in Paris!
    Absolutely fantastic experience, the venue is small which means there are no bad seats, it also means you don't end up feeling like cattle being herded, something which can't be said for other cabaret shows in Paris! The show itself is fantastic with really imaginative performances/routines with all the dancers perfectly in sync coupled with fantastic use of lighting to create a really artsy experience. There are a lot of breasts/flesh on show but again this is very tastefully done and not at all 'erotic', you could quite happily attend with (mature) teens, etc. This is the second time we've been with a 6 year gap in between and I'd happily go again.
    LE CRAZY HORSE PARIS

Fun show and experience in Paris
Oct 2024 • Couples
We decided to go to the Crazy Horse instead of Moulin Rouge, and we enjoyed the experience. The venue is clean and comfortable, and the show was enjoyable. The women were all quite talented and attractive, and the range of acts was interesting. I can't say I was mesmerized by the show, but if you have reasonable expectations it's a nice experience. One quibble is that we were at a VIP table, and the food offering at these tables is caviar. That's a pretty esoteric, acquired taste, and I saw several couples nearby not touch their food. It seems to me a more universally accepted food offering or snack would be more enjoyable.
